{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/x2.css">
{% endblock %}

{% set opening = card_data.cells["0.04|12|0.8|48|R"] %}
{% set comparison = card_data.cells["0.04|12|0.8|120|E"] %}

{% macro dial(name, label, values, active, numeric=True) %}
<div class="x2-dial" data-dial="{{ name }}">
  <span class="x2-dial__label">{{ label }}</span>
  <div class="x2-dial__options">
    {% for v in values %}
    {% set token = "%g"|format(v) if numeric else v %}
    <button type="button" class="x2-dial__btn{% if token == active %} x2-dial__btn--active{% endif %}"
            data-value="{{ token }}"
            aria-pressed="{{ 'true' if token == active else 'false' }}">{{ token }}</button>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro analytic_slot(name, label) %}
<article class="x2-analytic" data-analytic="{{ name }}">
  <div class="interval-stat" data-point="" data-lo="" data-hi="" data-verdict="noise">
    <span class="interval-stat__label">{{ label }}</span>
    <span class="interval-stat__value">&mdash;</span>
    <div class="interval-stat__rail">
      <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
      <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
    </div>
    <span class="interval-stat__range">95% band</span>
  </div>
  <div class="x2-analytic__meta">
    <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="noise">noise</span>
    {# numerics gate: the Wilson HW is on the cell's MEASURED POWER (the
       verdict's own MC uncertainty), not on the alpha/Sharpe band. #}
    <span class="x2-wilson">measured power carries a Wilson 95% half-width of &plusmn;<span class="x2-wilson__value">&mdash;</span> &mdash; the verdict is itself an estimate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title">power gate</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">no threshold reached in the measured range</p>
  </div>
</article>
{% endmacro %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="x2-intro">
  <p class="x2-headline">
    Choose the dials. Every claim is a precomputed cell of the X1 atlas &mdash; the page
    computes nothing, it snaps to measured rungs and never interpolates. Watch an interval
    widen, a verdict flip, a gate stay shut.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="x2-exhibit" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2 class="x2-exhibit__title">What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <p class="x2-exhibit__subhead">What you are looking at</p>
  <p class="x2-exhibit__lede">
    The page opens on one simulated manager at middling skill (IC 0.04), a 12-month alpha
    half-life, disciplined sizing, a 48-month track record, viewed at the returns-only tier
    (R). Its annualized alpha reads {{ "%.3f"|format(opening.alpha[0]) }}, but the 95% band runs from
    {% if opening.alpha[1] < 0 %}&minus;{% else %}+{% endif %}{{ "%.5f"|format(opening.alpha[1] | abs) }} to
    {% if opening.alpha[2] >= 0 %}+{% else %}&minus;{% endif %}{{ "%.4f"|format(opening.alpha[2] | abs) }}
    &mdash; it straddles zero, so the verdict is <em>noise</em>: forty-eight months cannot tell
    this manager from a lucky one. Select track length 120 and pin exposures (tier E): alpha is
    {{ "%.3f"|format(comparison.alpha[0]) }}, with a band from
    {% if comparison.alpha[1] >= 0 %}+{% else %}&minus;{% endif %}{{ "%.6f"|format(comparison.alpha[1] | abs) }} to
    {% if comparison.alpha[2] >= 0 %}+{% else %}&minus;{% endif %}{{ "%.5f"|format(comparison.alpha[2] | abs) }},
    and the verdict is <em>{{ comparison.alpha[3] }}</em>. Nothing is
    computed in your browser &mdash; each dial just opens a precomputed cell of the X1 atlas.
  </p>
  <p class="x2-exhibit__subhead">How to read it</p>
  <ul class="x2-exhibit__map">
    <li><b>Dials</b> are buttons, not sliders: they <em>snap</em> to computed cells, because the
      grid is measured, not modelled, and there is nothing honest to show between rungs.</li>
    <li><b>Interval band</b> &mdash; the shaded rail is the 95% credible band and the marker is the
      point estimate; wider means less certain. Watch it animate as you switch T.</li>
    <li><b>Verdict chip</b> &mdash; <em>noise</em> when the band covers zero, <em>shrink</em> for a
      smaller-than-headline effect, <em>robust</em> when the effect is clearly supported.</li>
    <li><b>Power gate</b> &mdash; open or shut; a shut gate (the tier-P trade analytics) names the
      trade threshold it failed, or says no threshold is reached in the measured range.</li>
    <li><b>Wilson footnote</b> &mdash; the &plusmn; half-width on the cell's measured power: the
      verdict is itself an estimate.</li>
    <li><b>False-alarm banner</b> &mdash; at IC = 0 there is no skill to find, so any detection is
      the false-alarm rate, not power.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="x2-exhibit__bridge">
    The full methodology &mdash; with the math and a reference implementation &mdash; is in the
    <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/x2.html">method spec</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="x2-controls" data-dials
         data-default-ic="0.04" data-default-half_life="12"
         data-default-sizing="0.8" data-default-T="48" data-default-tier="R">
  {{ dial("ic", "Information coefficient", card_data.meta.dials.ic, "0.04") }}
  {{ dial("half_life", "Alpha half-life (months)", card_data.meta.dials.half_life, "12") }}
  {{ dial("sizing", "Sizing discipline", card_data.meta.dials.sizing, "0.8") }}
  {{ dial("T", "Track length T (months)", card_data.meta.dials.T, "48") }}
  {{ dial("tier", "Transparency tier", card_data.meta.dials.tier, "R", numeric=False) }}
</section>

<div class="x2-falsealarm" data-falsealarm hidden>
  IC = 0: these figures are the <strong>false-alarm rate</strong> &mdash; detection where
  there is no skill, not power.
</div>

<section class="x2-analytics" data-analytics>
  {{ analytic_slot("alpha", "Annualized alpha") }}
  {{ analytic_slot("sharpe", "Sharpe ratio") }}
  {{ analytic_slot("hit_rate", "Hit rate (active batting average)") }}
  {{ analytic_slot("sizing_slope", "Sizing-curve slope (Fama–MacBeth mean b_t)") }}
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>The page is a communication device, not an analytic: it renders a precomputed subset of
the X1 atlas grid (450 cells, &ge;500 simulated managers each), shipped as committed JSON.
Dials snap to computed cells &mdash; interpolating between them would invent precision the
Monte-Carlo grid does not have.</p>
<p>The tier selector is the star control: the same ground truth at three honesty levels. R
estimates betas from returns; E pins them to the true exposures, narrowing the alpha band;
P adds trade-level analytics behind PowerGates. Every verdict rests on a measured power
that carries its own Wilson 95% half-width &mdash; the verdict is itself an estimate.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/x2-playground.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
